data.name: checkBoxMainFoodCols.ToolTip
data.value:
By default this CheckBox is initially checked.
In Unchecked state all fields in the food table are displayed in the below DataGrid.
In Checked state it only certain fields from the food table to be displayed in the below DataGrid. In particular only the nutritional information for Energy, Protein, Fat Total and Saturated, Carbohydrate, Sugars, Dietary Fibre and Sodium. The Id and Food description are always displayed.

data.name: textBoxFilter.ToolTip
data.value:
This TextBox accepts filter text.
Type in it and press the {Enter} key. The below DataGrid will then display only those foods whose <Food description> field contains the filter text. The filter text will clear and be displayed to the right and focus will transfer to the first row (if any) in the DataGrid. If there are no filter results, focus will remain in the (now empty) TextBox.
If no string is entered into this TextBox (ie. the {Enter} key is pressed without typing anything) then ALL Food data will be displayed in the below DataGrid, and the the text "Unfiltered" will display to its right.
